cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on the design and implementation of graph processing accelerators, which is a hardware architecture topic.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses parallel graph computation and runtime scheduling, which are core components of distributed and parallel computing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the design and implementation of a system for graph processing acceleration, which falls under the systems and control category.
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): Graph processing accelerators are emerging technologies that are gaining attention in the field of computer science.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): Although the paper focuses on hardware design, it also discusses benchmarks and results for evaluating a graph processing accelerator, which involves software engineering aspects.
